OL,3,CWhy schools must be the frontline of
OL,4,Cthe struggle against antisemitism
OL,6,FDuring a history lesson covering
OL,7,FHitler's Holocaust, a student deemed
OL,8,Fit "interesting" that "no country has
OL,9,Fever wanted the Jews." With this in
OL,10,Fmind, the child was confused as to
OL,11,Fwhy, then, "we don't blame the Jews."
OL,13,FHe reckoned: "They must be doing
OL,14,Fsomething wrong."
OL,16,FI regularly remind students that Jews
OL,17,Fdid not, and do not, "steal all the
OL,18,Fmoney!"
OL,26,@uD@NOUvD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
