OL,3,CWhy schools must be the frontline of
OL,4,Cthe struggle against antisemitism
OL,6,FI was, above all else, distressed to
OL,7,Fcatch students emailing each other
OL,8,Fpictures of Orthodox Jews "as a joke"
OL,9,Fbecause "they look funny."
OL,11,FThis, more than anything else,
OL,12,Ffrightens me. For, in mockery of
OL,13,Fsomething as basic as appearance, a
OL,14,Fline is crossed; misinformation is
OL,15,Fdwarfed by the purest, most ancient
OL,16,Fform of contempt: one that lessons on
OL,17,Feconomics or history will struggle to
OL,18,Fdefeat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
